  5 previous_accounting_numeraire_weight

Potential concern:
  Some global features may need transformation/normalization before a serious
  actor network. In particular, raw equity magnitude may be a scale issue. We
  need review on whether the `.net`/feature manifest should specify transforms,
  normalization policy, and named feature blocks rather than only dimensions.

Current raw policy output and action distribution
-------------------------------------------------

raw_policy_output_t:

  schema_id =
    kikijyeba.environment.raw_policy_output.target_node_weights_logits.v1
  action_adapter_id = target_node_weights_simplex.v1
  action_distribution_id = masked_dirichlet_simplex.v1
  node_weight_logits[A]
  action_distribution_params
  value_estimate

action_distribution_iface_t:

  distribution_id()
  sample(raw, input, adapter_options, distribution_options)
  deterministic_action(raw, input, adapter_options, distribution_options)
  log_prob(raw, input, action, evidence, distribution_options)
  entropy(raw, input, evidence, distribution_options)
  approximate_kl(old_record, new_record)

Current distributions:

  masked_dirichlet_simplex_distribution_t
    - active nodes = valid & tradable & executable
    - K=0 fails closed
    - K=1 deterministic weight 1, log_prob 0, entropy 0
    - K>1 softmax logits -> mean, concentration -> alpha, sample Dirichlet
    - inactive nodes exactly zero
    - evidence includes alpha_active, mean_active, total_concentration,
      sampled_active_weights, log_prob, entropy, value_estimate

  masked_logistic_normal_simplex_distribution_t
    - supported as candidate
    - uses active additive log-ratio coordinates
    - has latent-normal entropy semantics
    - should be treated as endpoint candidate pending math/evidence review

